NAME
  opm - Aurora package manager

SYNOPSIS
  opm <command> [args]

DESCRIPTION
  Installs, removes and updates packages from GitHub-hosted registries. Each
  package file is verified against a sha256 checksum and written atomically.

COMMANDS
  update                 refresh package lists from the configured sources
  search <query>         search available packages
  info <name>            show details about a package
  install <name[@ver]>   install packages and their dependencies
  remove <name>          uninstall packages (refuses if depended upon)
  list                   list installed packages
  outdated               list installed packages that have a newer version
  why <name>             show which installed packages depend on <name>
  upgrade                upgrade all installed packages
  freeze [-o FILE]       write a lockfile of installed packages (pins versions)
  restore <FILE>         install the exact packages from a lockfile

OPTIONS
  -f, --force            reinstall/remove even when not strictly needed
  --fresh                bypass the cache and re-fetch indexes

FILES
  /etc/opm/sources.lua          registry sources
  /etc/opm/installed/<pkg>.json local package manifests

EXAMPLES
  opm update && opm install acowsay
  opm remove acowsay
  opm freeze -o packages.lock      # snapshot the current package set
  opm restore packages.lock        # reproduce it on another machine
